comments: Zeller (CHA) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Schroder's (LAL) path and does not deliver any contact.
As Kuzma (LAL) releases his dribble, his off-arm makes marginal contact with Graham (CHA).
Martin (CHA) legally contests Kuzma's (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Zeller (CHA) and Drummond (LAL) mutually clamp each others' arms and affect their FOM.
Drummond (LAL) makes contact with the ball during the steal. Any additional arm contact is marginal.
Drummond (LAL) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Martin's (CHA) path and does not deliver any contact.
Drummond (LAL) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Martin's (CHA) path.
Drummond (LAL) makes marginal contact with Bridges' (CHA) left arm after Bridges removes his left hand from the ball to pass.
Caruso (LAL) legally contests Graham's (CHA) jump shot attempt.
Graham (CHA) commits a take foul on Caruso (LAL).
Graham (CHA) is not established in Schroder's (LAL) path and is still moving laterally when contact occurs on Schroder's dribble that affects his SQBR.

As both players fall to the floor to pursue the loose ball, Zeller (CHA) makes marginal contact with Schroder's (LAL) head/upper body. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Zeller's (CHA) leg makes incidental contact with the ball while the ball is loose.
McDaniels (CHA) commits a take foul on Kuzma (LAL).
Zeller (CHA) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Caruso's (LAL) path.
Caruso (LAL) legally contests Graham's (CHA) jump shot attempt.
Drummond (LAL) does not make any contact with Zeller (CHA) that affects his ability to rebound.
Bridges (CHA) commits a take foul on Kuzma (LAL).
